a cloud badge as a secondary badge besides a local badge. [For cloud-only products] we can’t guarantee it will work if they turn off the cloud one day.” "},"dropcap":false,"endmark":false,"lead":false},{"__typename":"EntryBodyParagraph","contents":{"html":"\u003cstrong\u003eMore voice control hardware\u003c/strong\u003e"},"dropcap":false,"endmark":false,"lead":false},{"__typename":"EntryBodyParagraph","contents":{"html":"Work on a \u003ca href=\"https://www.home-assistant.io/blog/2022/12/20/year-of-voice/\"\u003elocally-based Home Assistant voice assistant\u003c/a\u003e that began last year is continuing, and a Home Assistant voice assistant hardware device is being developed. “We want to make our own hardware that people can put in their homes and replace Google and Amazon with,” says Schoutsen. The device should arrive at the end of this year, he says, hinting at a future screen-based device. “We are looking at screens, nothing official to announce, but we’re looking at E-ink. We don’t need color, as we don’t need ads.” "},"dropcap":false,"endmark":false,"lead":false},{"__typename":"EntryBodyParagraph","contents":{"html":"\u003cstrong\u003eMore AI\u003c/strong\u003e"},"dropcap":false,"endmark":false,"lead":false},{"__typename":"EntryBodyParagraph","contents":{"html":"Home Assistant is exploring incorporating generative AI into home automation but, crucially, \u003ca href=\"https://www.linkedin.com/posts/schoutsen_jetson-ai-lab-research-group-activity-7181139740522336256-k2EX/\"\u003eusing local processing\u003c/a\u003e. “Some people are using ChatGPT with Home Assistant, but it’s so slow,” says Schoutsen. They are \u003ca href=\"https://www.linkedin.com/posts/schoutsen_excited-to-have-ollama-running-onboard-jetson-activity-7184294951994691586-l0RB/\"\u003eworking with Nvidia\u003c/a\u003e to use its \u003ca href=\"https://developer.nvidia.com/blog/bringing-generative-ai-to-life-with-jetson/\"\u003eJetson\u003c/a\u003e platform to power LLMs for Home Assistant."},"